parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Incorrect odometer readings can lead to unfair sales practices, affecting the vehicle's value and potentially causing financial losses for buyers.
symptoms: discrepancy between odometer reading and title mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty design of the cooling system can cause the supply hose to come loose, leading to engine overheating, damage, and potential engine failure, which can result in accidents or strand the driver.
Anti-freeze leaks can cause engine damage, overheating, and corrosion, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
Defective seat belts can fail to provide adequate protection in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
The failure of the fuel tank strap can cause the fuel tank to become dislodged, leading to fuel leaks, fires, and accidents.
symptoms: The fuel tank strap is broken or hanging loose
the fuel tank is not properly secured.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge sending unit can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate fuel level readings, stranding, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The fuel gauge is not accurate
the fuel gauge is stuck on a particular reading
the vehicle runs out of fuel unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel line leaks can cause fuel to spill onto the engine or other hot surfaces, leading to fires, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel lines
fuel smell inside or outside the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Body Control Module (BCM) can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, including door locks, windows, and horn, potentially trapping occupants inside the vehicle.
Water intrusion into the Engine Control Module (ECM) can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, especially in rainy conditions, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or fails to start

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manual transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or become stuck in gear, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission jumps out of gear
the vehicle is unable to move or accelerate
the vehicle requires high RPMs to move

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage properly can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or become stuck in gear, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission does not engage into gear
the vehicle is unable to move or accelerate
the vehicle requires high RPMs to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake light switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake light illuminates on the dashboard
the brake light bulbs burn out
the brake light switch needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty door lock/opening mechanism can cause the door to become stuck or unable to open, potentially trapping occupants inside the vehicle.
symptoms: The door is unable to open from both inside and outside
the door lock mechanism is faulty.
